snippet: With the parliamentary victory, Iran’s supreme leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, is expected to eliminate the presidency after Mahmoud Ahmadinejad’s term expires next year.
abstract: Supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei's allies win the bulk of seats in Iran's parliamentary elections; Khamenei, who has jousted repeatedly with Pres Mahmoud Ahmadinejad, is expected to eliminate the presidential post entirely.

byline.contributor: Artin Afkhami contributed reporting from Boston.

lead_paragraph: With the parliamentary victory, Iran’s supreme leader, Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, is expected to eliminate the presidency after Mahmoud Ahmadinejad’s term expires next year.

headline.seo: Iran Elections Deal Blow to Ahmadinejad and the Presidency
headline.main: Elections in Iran Favor Ayatollah’s Allies, Dealing Blow to President and His Office
headline.print_headline: Elections in Iran Favor Ayatollah’s Allies, Dealing Blow to President and His Office
